name: Consistent Care Services- COVID Vaccine Site
notes:
***This is a clinic for 1st or 2nd doses of the Pfizer or Moderna COVID-19 vaccine*** All patients 12 years old and older can register for the Pfizer vaccine only. (If 12-17 years old for the Pfizer vaccine, you must be with a parent or guardian or have parental/guardian consent) Vaccinations at the Consistent Care Services COVID Vaccine Clinic are by appointment only. The clinic is located at 1235 N. Post St., Spokane WA 99201. The clinic is located upstairs in suite 201. There is elevator access or stairs. 
***Residents of ANY state are now eligible for the vaccine, but you still must have photo ID***
***Parking is free on the West side of the building only in stalls 14-55. Please do not come to your appointment if you are sick*** 
***Please no outside food or drinks***  
*VERY IMPORTANT*
***Please complete all the insurance/Medicare/Medicaid information when registering online for your appointment to avoid filling it out at the clinic***WE WILL HOWEVER NEED TO SCAN AN INSURANCE CARD AS WELL IF YOU HAVE ONE, these are two different steps on our end,

Thank you…
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Thurston County Public Health Medical Reserve Corp

address.street1: Rainier Senior Center - 108 Michigan St S

notes: This is a Pfizer vaccination event for anyone age 12 and older. This is a walk-in clinic at Rainier Senior Center located at 108 Michigan st S, Rainier, WA 98576, for anyone age 12 and older from 1pm-5pm. All minors 12 to 17 years old must receive parent or guardian consent to receive a COVID-19 vaccine. This must be done in PrepMod when registering for an appointment. Parents or guardians do not have to be present at the time of vaccination if they signed the consent form online during registration. • Please bring a form of identification with you to your appointment - ID card, passport, or other document with your name and birthday on it. • Wear a short-sleeved shirt, but dress with layers if necessary. • Waiting at least 15 minutes after vaccination is required.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.

name: Walla Walla County HD- COVID Provider
notes:
**THIS CLINIC IS BY APPOINTMENT FOR 1st & 2nd DOSE PFIZER VACCINATIONS for all qualifying individuals aged 12 years & over. Walk-ins are welcome. Parental/Guardian consent is required for 12 – 17 year olds, parent/guardian consent and signature can be completed on-site or in the final screen of the online registration process. Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) vaccine is also available for people 18 years and older. This clinic is at the Providence Southgate Medical Park main building (the former Walla Walla General Hospital) 1025 South 2nd Ave. Participants are advised to stay to their right as they enter the campus and proceed to the main entrance, instead of going to Urgent Care. COVID vaccine is not available in Urgent Care.
Masks are required. If you do not have a mask, one will be provided.
We look forward to seeing you. Thanks for keeping Walla Walla well.

** ESTA CLÍNICA ES CON CITA PARA LAS VACUNAS DE LA 1ª y 2ª DOSIS DE PFIZER para personas calificadas de 12 años en Adelante. Se requiere el consentimiento de los padres / tutores para los jóvenes de 12 - 17 años, las firmas y el consentimiento en la pantalla de registro final.  La vacuna Janssen (Johnson & Johnson) también está disponible para personas mayores de 18 años.** Esto será en el edificio principal de Providence Southgate Medical Park, (antes conocido como el Hospital General de Walla Walla)1025 Sur 2nd ave.  Se recomienda a los participantes que se mantengan a su derecha al ingresar y que se dirijan a la entrada principal, en lugar de ir a Atención de Urgencia.  La Vacuna COVID no está disponible en Atención de Urgencias. **
El cubre bocas es requerido. Si no tiene un cubre bocas, se le proporcionará una.  
BIENVENIDO A WALK-INS. Esperamos verlo. Gracias por cuidar a Walla Walla.
If you are signing up for a second dose, you must get the same vaccine brand as your first dose.
